.TH nis_server 3NSL "10 Nov 2005" "SunOS 5.11" "Networking Services Library Functions"
.SH NAME
nis_server, nis_mkdir, nis_rmdir, nis_servstate, nis_stats,
nis_getservlist, nis_freeservlist, nis_freetags \- miscellaneous NIS+
functions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
\fBcc\fR [ \fIflag\fR.\|.\|. ] \fIfile\fR.\|.\|. \fB-lnsl\fR [ \fIlibrary\fR.\|.\|. ]
#include <rpcsvc/nis.h>

\fBnis_error\fR \fBnis_mkdir\fR(\fBnis_name\fR \fIdirname\fR, \fBnis_server *\fImachine\fR);
.fi

.LP
.nf
\fBnis_error\fR \fBnis_rmdir\fR(\fBnis_name\fR \fIdirname\fR, \fBnis_server *\fImachine\fR);
.fi

.LP
.nf
\fBnis_error\fR \fBnis_servstate\fR(\fBnis_server *\fImachine\fR, \fBnis_tag *\fItags\fR, \fBint\fR \fInumtags\fR,
     \fBnis_tag **\fIresult\fR);
.fi

.LP
.nf
\fBnis_error\fR \fBnis_stats\fR(\fBnis_server *\fImachine\fR, \fBnis_tag *\fItags\fR, \fBint\fR \fInumtags\fR,
     \fBnis_tag **\fIresult\fR);
.fi

.LP
.nf
\fBvoid\fR \fBnis_freetags\fR(\fBnis_tag *\fItags\fR, \fBint\fR \fInumtags\fR);
.fi

.LP
.nf
\fBnis_server **\fBnis_getservlist\fR(\fBnis_name\fR \fIdirname\fR);
.fi

.LP
.nf
\fBvoid\fR \fBnis_freeservlist\fR(\fBnis_server **\fImachines\fR);
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
These functions provide a variety of services for NIS+ applications.
.sp
.LP
The \fBnis_mkdir()\fR function is used to create the necessary databases to
support NIS+ service for a directory, \fIdirname\fR, on a server,
\fImachine\fR. If this operation is successful, it means that the directory
object describing \fIdirname\fR has been updated to reflect that server
\fImachine\fR is serving the named directory. For a description of the
\fBnis_server\fR structure, refer to \fBnis_objects\fR(3NSL).
.sp
.LP
Per-server and per-directory access restrictions can apply to the
\fBnis_mkdir()\fR function. See \fBnisopaccess\fR(1).
.sp
.LP
The \fBnis_rmdir()\fR function is used to delete the directory,
\fIdirname\fR, from the specified server machine. The \fImachine\fR
parameter cannot be \fINULL\fR. The \fBnis_rmdir()\fR function does not
remove the directory \fIdirname\fR from the namespace or remove a server
from the server list in the directory object. To remove a directory from the
namespace you must call \fBnis_remove()\fR to remove the directory
\fBdirname\fR from the namespace and call the\fBnis_rmdir()\fR for each
server in the server list to remove the directory from the server. To remove
a replica from the server list, you need to first call \fBnis_modify()\fR to
remove the server from the directory object and then call \fBnis_rmdir()\fR
to remove the replica.
.sp
.LP
Per-server and per-directory access restrictions can apply to
\fBnis_rmdir()\fR. See \fBnisopaccess\fR(1).
.sp
.LP
For a description of the \fBnis_server\fR structure, refer to
\fBnis_objects\fR(3NSL).
.sp
.LP
The \fBnis_servstate()\fR function is used to set and read the various
state variables of the NIS+ servers. In particular the internal debugging
state of the servers can be set and queried.
.sp
.LP
The \fBnis_stats()\fR function is used to retrieve statistics about how the
server is operating. Tracking these statistics can help administrators
determine when they need to add additional replicas or to break up a domain
into two or more subdomains. For more information on reading statistics, see
\fBnisstat\fR(1M)
.sp
.LP
The \fBnis_servstate()\fR and \fBnis_stats()\fR functions use the tag list.
The tag list is a variable length array of \fInis_tag\fR structures whose
length is passed to the function in the \fInumtags\fR parameter. The set of
legal tags are defined in the file <\fBrpcsvc/nis_tags.h\fR> which is
included in <\fBrpcsvc/nis.h\fR>. Because these tags can and do vary between
implementations of the NIS+ service, it is best to consult this file for the
supported list. Passing unrecognized tags to a server will result in their
\fItag_value\fR member being set to the string \fBunknown\fR. Both of these
functions return their results in malloced tag structure, \fI*result\fR. If
there is an error, \fI*result\fR is set to \fINULL\fR. The \fItag_value\fR
pointers points to allocated string memory which contains the results. Use
\fBnis_freetags()\fR to free the tag structure.
.sp
.LP
Per-server and per-directory access restrictions can apply to the
\fBNIS_SERVSTATE\fR or \fBNIS_STATUS\fR (\fBnis_stats()\fR) operations and
their sub-operations (\fItags\fR). See \fBnisopaccess\fR(1).
.sp
.LP
The \fBnis_getservlist()\fR function returns a null terminated list of
\fInis_server\fR structures that represent the list of servers that serve
the domain named \fIdirname\fR. Servers from this list can be used when
calling functions that require the name of a NIS+ server. For a description
of the \fBnis_server\fR refer to \fBnis_objects\fR(3NSL).
\fBnis_freeservlist()\fR frees the list of servers list of servers returned
by \fBnis_getservlist()\fR. Note that this is the only legal way to free
that list.
